            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10142",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sloat",
                        "name": "sloat",
                        "displayName": "Matt Schmidt",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Checking the data in Zend_Db_Table::fetch(Row|All) would work. Having Zend_Db_Table_Row::__construct throw an exception would be unnecessary, IMHO.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sloat",
                        "name": "sloat",
                        "displayName": "Matt Schmidt",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-06-22T10:05:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-06-22T10:05:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11151",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wizkid",
                        "name": "wizkid",
                        "displayName": "Emil Hesslow",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Wouldn't it be smarter to change the function to:\n{code}\npublic function fetchRow($where = null, $order = null)\n{\n    $data = $this->_fetch('Row', $where, $order, 1);\n    if ($data === false)\n        return null;\n\n    return new Zend_Db_Table_Row(array(\n        'db'    => $this->_db,\n        'table' => $this,\n        'data'  => $data,\n    ));\n}\n{code}\n\nThis would mean that you get null returned if there is no row. Because if one want a new row you just use newRow(). Or have I misunderstood something?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wizkid",
                        "name": "wizkid",
                        "displayName": "Emil Hesslow",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-11-04T20:12:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-11-04T20:12:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11446",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Changing fix version to 0.8.0.",
