                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12675",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Nick Thornley writes (2007-02-11):\n\nI'm just wondering what other people are doing to check if a row object has been populated, as my first thought is that an exists() method would be a useful, just as see there is in Zend_Db_Table_Rowset?\n\nfor example, if you have just returned a Row object from a Zend_Db_table object it would be nice to do:\n\n{code}\n$row = $Table_User->find(1);\nif ( !$row->exists() ) {\n    \/\/no result\n}\n{code}\n\nNick ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-11T11:59:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-11T11:59:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13399",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "As of revision 3995, the find() method always returns an object of type Zend_Db_Table_Rowset_Abstract.\n\nTherefore you can use an exists() method to find out if the find() method returned any rows.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-15T23:36:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-15T23:36:43.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13498",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wizkid",
                        "name": "wizkid",
                        "displayName": "Emil Hesslow",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Can I ask why it can't just return null? I must say that I haven't used ZF that much but when I have there is very rare that I need a object row if find() don't find anything. And if I do need a new object row I can just call fetchNew(). Probably in more then 90% of the cases I have no need for the empty row object.\n\nI my self have used the code I posted before that just returns null if there isn't exist any row object. Very easy to check and I don't get any empty row object that I don't use.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wizkid",
                        "name": "wizkid",
                        "displayName": "Emil Hesslow",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-18T17:45:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-18T17:45:43.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13515",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Yes, I will make the following changes:\n\nZend_Db_Table_Abstract::fetchRow() returns a Zend_Db_Table_Row_Abstract object, or else null if no rows are found.\n\nZend_Db_Table_Abstract::find() and fetchAll() each return a Zend_Db_Table_Rowset_Abstract object.  This object has a method called exists() for testing if the rowset is empty.\n\nZend_Db_Table_Row_Abstract::findDependentRowset() returns a Zend_Db_Table_Rowset_Abstract object.  \n\nZend_Db_Table_Row_Abstract::findParentRow() returns a Zend_Db_Table_Row_Abstract object, or else null if no rows are found (though the latter case should never happen in a database with referential integrity).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-19T12:06:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-19T12:06:02.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13516",
                    "author": {
